<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1029" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1029">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Bowen</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-06-14"><hi rend="italic">June 14,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Bowen reports that the manager of the Bermudez Company informs him
                            that the Venezuelan Government threatens suit unless the company pay
                            $10,000,000 to the Venezuelan Government. He advised him to pay nothing,
                            to defend their rights in court, and to publish facts; thinks the
                            company’s policy should be honest and fearless.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>